HEADWORD: Maggot
<hw>Mag"got</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[W. <ets>macai</ets>,
pl. <ets>maceiod</ets>, <ets>magiod</ets>, a worn or grub; cf.
<ets>magu</ets> to bread.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The
footless larva of any fly. See <er>Larval</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A whim; an odd fancy.</def> <rj><au>Hudibras.
Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maggotiness</ent>⟦br⟧
